content.description: No crux really just a fun 25 ft of climbing.
content.location: Left of the Squirrel Project is a climb with a small dihedral on the upper half.

content.description: Crux right in the middle of the wall.
content.location: Start on the face right of "Flying Fish" trending a bit right to small overhang, some variations but all the same grade.

climbs.name: Squirrel Nuts
climbs.fa: Kevin Baker (bouldering), Pete Cleveland and Alex A TR

content.description: The king line of the crag IMO.Starting with a few easier moves on big holds, you will quickly find yourself off the ground a bit and trying to pull a tricky roof.  High feet and pinches likely will be useful.  Gain the slab and finish it up.  A proud line, no doubt.
content.location: Far west end of February Wall.

content.description: Start at an inside corner crack, climb like a dihedral. Crack leads to an awkward overhang, the crux. Get past that and it's smooth sailing.
content.protection: We built top rope anchors above climb.
content.location: The west side of February Wall, just left of a curved rock wall. 50 feet west of Bread and Jam.

content.description: Low crux while pulling around the roof and eases off towards the top.
content.location: Find the corner overhang right of "Stride Right", Leap Year starts just left of the overhang and passes the overhang on the left to a stance over it.

content.description: You start on a rounded corner which seemed more slab than corner, and finish in the groove above. Very straight forward, fun climb. Left of Phooey. Route was not named in "Climber's Guide To Devil's Lake" so I gave it this name. Since it sits next to Phooey, these two climbs become "Hong Kong Phooey."
content.protection: We top roped it above climb.
content.location: West end of February wall, left of Phooey. About 45 feet west of Bread & Jam.

content.description: Crux right in the middle as the wide crack zags right. Good warm up.
content.protection: We bouldered it but a rope can't hurt. The crux is in the safe fall zone.
content.location: Wide cracks in the middle of the wall.

content.description: Eh, it's a warm up. Left wall is off. Go direct for better climbing in the same grade just right of the corner.
content.protection: We bouldered it but those less confident will want a rope.
content.location: First corner worth climbing from the west approach.

content.description: # 20 in Climbers Guide, farthest right of three cracks.
Fun finger crack on the first half that widens to hang jams at the top. Finish straight up the crack or go right at the ledge halfway for a more secure bouldering finish.
content.protection: Pads or some nuts and cams for the top.
content.location: Obvious crack straight up the wall in the middle of February Wall, 20ft right of "Leap Year".

content.description:
Short but difficult, not a lot of solid holds, tiny knobs mostly. Really takes some thought to figure out the problem. Old Timer named Bill got every climber up the route, but without his help we all kept falling. 

  #11 on page 60 of 3rd Edition Climbers Guide to Devils Lake
content.location: The west side of February Wall, 10 feet left of Bread and Jam

pathTokens: East Bluff 02 - East of the Quarry

content.description: Short wall easily found off the Ice Age Trail.
